structed in response to the situational circumstances of talk-in-interaction) and emergent (i.e. constructed with regard to symbolic units as parts of socially and culturally shared knowledge).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aFunctional discourse grammar. 4aDialogizität. 4aGesprochene Sprache. 4aGrammatik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aDialogue.  aGrammar.  aSpoken Language.1 aAnward, Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarth-Weingarten, Dagmar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBücker, Jörg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBücker, Jörg, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCouper-Kuhlen, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeppermann, Arnulf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFox, Barbara A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGünthner, Susanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGünthner, Susanne, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHopper, Paul J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aImo, Wolfgang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aImo, Wolfgang, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKönig, Katharina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLinell, Per, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMertzlufft, Christine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPfänder, Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSkrovec, Marie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabul